fields.title: Addresses
fields.description: Location of properties based on address identifiers, usually by road name, house number, postal code.

fields.title: Administrative units
fields.description: Units of administration, dividing areas where Member States have and/or exercise jurisdictional rights, for local, regional and national governance, separated by administrative boundaries.

fields.title: Cadastral parcels
fields.description: Areas defined by cadastral registers or equivalent.

fields.title: Geographical grid system
fields.description: Harmonised multi-resolution grid with a common point of origin and standardised location and size of grid cells.

fields.title: Geographical names
fields.description: Names of areas, regions, localities, cities, suburbs, towns or settlements, or any geographical or topographical feature of public or historical interest.

fields.title: Hydrography
fields.description: Hydrographic elements, including marine areas and all other water bodies and items related to them, including river basins and sub-basins.

fields.title: Protected sites
fields.description: Area designated or managed within a framework of international, Community and Member States' legislation to achieve specific conservation objectives.

fields.title: Coordinate reference systems
fields.description: Systems for uniquely referencing spatial information in space as a set of coordinates (x, y, z) and/or latitude and longitude and height, based on a geodetic horizontal and vertical datum.

fields.title: Transport networks
fields.description: Road, rail, air and water transport networks and related infrastructure. Includes links between different networks.

fields.title: Elevation
fields.description: Digital elevation models for land, ice and ocean surface. Includes terrestrial elevation, bathymetry and shoreline.

fields.title: Geology
fields.description: Geology characterised according to composition and structure. Includes bedrock, aquifers and geomorphology.

fields.title: Land cover
fields.description: Physical and biological cover of the earth's surface including artificial surfaces, agricultural areas, forests, (semi-)natural areas, wetlands, water bodies.

fields.title: Orthoimagery
fields.description: Geo-referenced image data of the Earth's surface, from either satellite or airborne sensors.

fields.title: Atmospheric conditions
fields.description: Physical conditions in the atmosphere. Includes spatial data based on measurements, on models or on a combination thereof and includes measurement locations.

fields.title: Agricultural and acquaculture facilities
fields.description: Farming equipment and production facilities (including irrigation systems, greenhouses and stables).

fields.title: Area management, restriction and regulation
fields.description: Areas managed, regulated or used for reporting at international, European, national, regional and local levels.

fields.title: Bio-geographical regions
fields.description: Areas of relatively homogeneous ecological conditions with common characteristics.

fields.title: Buildings
fields.description: Geographical location of buildings.

fields.title: Environmental monitoring facilities
fields.description: Location and operation of environmental monitoring facilities includes observation and measurement of emissions, of the state of environmental media and of other ecosystem parameters.

fields.title: Energy resources
fields.description: Energy resources including hydrocarbons, hydropower, bio-energy, solar, wind, etc., where relevant including depth/height information on the extent of the resource.

fields.title: Habitats and biotopes
fields.description: Geographical areas characterised by specific ecological conditions, processes, structure, and (life support) functions that physically support the organisms that live there.

fields.title: Human health and safety
fields.description: Geographical distribution of dominance of pathologies (allergies, cancers, respiratory diseases, etc.), information indicating the effect on health (biomarkers, decline of fertility, epidemics) or well-being of humans.

fields.title: Land use
fields.description: Territory characterised according to its current and future planned functional dimension or socio-economic purpose (e.g. residential, industrial, commercial, agricultural, forestry, recreational).

fields.title: Meteorological geographical features
fields.description: Weather conditions and their measurements.

fields.title: Mineral resources
fields.description: Mineral resources including metal ores, industrial minerals, etc., where relevant including depth/height information on the extent of the resource.

fields.title: Natural risk zones
fields.description: Vulnerable areas characterised according to natural hazards (all atmospheric, hydrologic, seismic, volcanic and wildfire phenomena that, because of their location, severity, and frequency, have the potential to seriously affect society).

fields.title: Oceanographic geographical features
fields.description: Physical conditions of oceans (currents, salinity, wave heights, etc.).

fields.title: Population distribution - demography
fields.description: Geographical distribution of people, including population characteristics and activity levels, aggregated by grid, region, administrative unit or other analytical unit.

fields.title: Production and industrial facilities
fields.description: Industrial production sites, including installations covered by Council Directive 96/61/EC of 24 September 1996 concerning integrated pollution prevention and control and water abstraction facilities, mining, storage sites.

fields.title: Species distribution
fields.description: Geographical distribution of occurrence of animal and plant species aggregated by grid, region, administrative unit or other analytical unit.

fields.title: Soil
fields.description: Soils and subsoil characterised according to depth, texture, structure and content of particles and organic material, stoniness, erosion, where appropriate mean slope and anticipated water storage capacity.

fields.title: Sea regions
fields.description: Physical conditions of seas and saline water bodies divided into regions and sub-regions with common characteristics.

fields.title: Statistical units
fields.description: Units for dissemination or use of statistical information.

fields.title: Utility and governmental services
fields.description: Includes utility facilities such as sewage, waste management, energy supply and water supply, administrative and social governmental services such as public administrations, civil protection sites, schools and hospitals.
